This paper deals with the task of post-editing machine-generated visual stories, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with CV. The paper also discusses the use of state-of-the-art models and the need for new automatic metrics, which suggests that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of data and the establishment of baselines, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
